The litanies for springtime were not employed in Spain, but litanies were used there in the beginning of N ovemben5 at the time of sowing the seed. These were not the only litanies in use. They were also employed, according to the locality, on the fast of Pentecostfi and at the autumnal equinox.⁷

10. Calendars and Martyroloffles.

The festivals celebrated every year were noted in the local calendar. Each Church must have possessed its own. The most ancient which have come down to us are those of Rome, Tours, and Garthage.8
